name: Indy 500
summary: The 2024 Indianapolis 500 faced a four-hour rain delay before finally starting at 4:44 p.m. ET. Josef Newgarden emerged victorious, securing his second consecutive Indy 500 win and the 20th overall for Roger Penske. Kyle Larson, who attempted to compete in both the Indy 500 and the Coca-Cola 600 on the same day, faced challenges due to the weather delay. Experts had predicted Colton Herta as a potential winner, but Newgarden's triumph upset those predictions. The event featured live updates from various locations within the Indianapolis Motor Speedway, including the Snake Pit, Coke Lot, and infield. Helio Castroneves, a four-time Indy 500 winner, aimed to make history with another victory. The race also drew attention to Kyle Larson's Indy 500 debut, representing NASCAR in the iconic event.
